  "local_port": 33684,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How big is Seattle compared to other American cities?",
  "response": "Seattle is the 18th largest city in the United States based on population. According to the United States Census Bureau, as of July 2021, Seattle has a population of approximately 737,015 people. In terms of land area, Seattle covers about 83.9 square miles (217.3 km2), ranking it 137th among U.S. cities in terms of size.\n\nHere is a brief comparison with a few other major U.S. cities:\n\n1. **New York City, New York**\n   - Population: Approximately 8.3 million\n   - Land Area: 300.5 square miles (778.3 km2)\n\n2. **Los Angeles, California**\n   - Population: Approximately 3.9 million\n   - Land Area: 468.7 square miles (1,213.9 km2)\n\n3. **Chicago, Illinois**\n   - Population: Approximately 2.7 million\n   - Land Area: 227.3 square miles (588.7 km2)\n\n4. **Houston, Texas**\n   - Population: Approximately 2.3 million\n   - Land Area: 637.5 square miles (1,651.2 km2)\n\n5. **Phoenix, Arizona**\n   - Population: Approximately 1.6 million\n   - Land Area: 517.6 square miles (1,340.6 km2)\n\n6. **San Francisco, California**\n   - Population: Approximately 874,961\n   - Land Area: 46.9 square miles (121.4 km2)\n\n7. **Denver, Colorado**\n   - Population: Approximately 715,522\n   - Land Area: 153.3 square miles (397.0 km2)\n\nIn summary, Seattle is a significant city in the U.S. in terms of population, but it's relatively smaller in terms of land area when compared to some of the largest cities in the country.",
